This paper discusses the use of multiple radio access technologies (RATs) in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). It also presents a theoretical framework for packet distribution and scheduling, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. The proposed system architecture and management processes are related to systems and control (cs.SY) and security and privacy (cs.CR).
